Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add the @brown rice{1.5%cup} and boil
for ~{25-30%minutes}, until tender. When finished, drain the rice, just like pasta.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and finely dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). 
Dice the @roma tomatoes{4}(diced). Drain and rinse the @black beans{2%box}. Zest, then halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved).

In a #shallow dish{}, combine the @smoked paprika{2%teaspoon}, half the lime zest, and a
large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Cut the @chicken thighs{24%ounce} into
bite-sized pieces and toss into the spice mixture. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan
and cook, tossing for ~{5-6%minutes}, until browned and cooked through. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Add the onions to the same pan over medium heat. If the pan is too dry, add another drizzle of
olive oil. Cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add a splash of water to help scrape
up the browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Remove the pan from heat.

When the rice is done, toss into the pan along with the onions, tomatoes, black beans, and spiced chicken.
Toss over medium heat until heated through. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice, a large drizzle of
olive oil, and the remaining lime zest. Season generously with salt and pepper, enjoy!

> Lime zest and paprika adds both brightness and smokiness to this weeknight chicken dish. Boneless, skinless
> thighs stay super juicy, giving this dish extra flavor. We love that everything gets tossed together at the
> end—it helps all the flavors marry!